{
  "text": "Of particular interest are the Doushantuo specimens that have been interpreted as bilaterians. These include a suite of specimens interpreted as embryonic bilaterians on the basis of endodermal cords [CITATION_1] , polar lobes [CITATION_2] , embryonic polarity [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] and duet cleavage [CITATION_5] . In each case, the specimens in question are more plausibly interpreted as cleavage specimens that have undergone taphonomic and diagenetic processes.",
  "correct_citation": {
